The paper deals with paging algorithms, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science. The focus is on the access graph model, which is a well-studied model in the area of online algorithms and competitive analysis. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces new concepts related to locality of reference and probabilistic data structures, which are relevant to cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses competitive analysis, which is a common technique in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
